\noindent{\bf Confusing Predicates.}
Another common case is that the LLM generates valid O values that are not in the proper relation P with subject S.
The most interesting situation here is when that incorrect O is in relation with S for another predicate Q ({{2405.02732_FO0082||FO}} P)
(e.g., Dumbledore appearing among Harry Potter's parents instead of being a friend).